    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1903</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 653.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring further to my telegram of November 15
                    last, I am unable to report any material change in the situation of school and
                    other unsettled qnestions.</p>
                <p>The grand vizier and the minister for foreign affairs spend very little time at
                    the Porte these days, and when I do succeed in seeing them I am politely put off
                    on the score that nothing can be done until after Ramazan.</p>
                <p>In the absence of any instruction from the Department I continue the patient but
                    persistent role I have been playing since January, at same time exerting every
                    effort to preserve the friendly relations which, I am happy to say, remain
                    unchanged, despite the rather complicated and disturbed conditions. So that I am
                    in position to pursue any line of policy that the Department may dictate.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John G. A. Leishman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
